# Version bump

One source of truth for the project version. The version is declared in four
places that must never drift apart:

- `cli/Cargo.toml` — the `jd` crate (`[package] version`)
- `core/Cargo.toml` — the `justdown` crate (`[package] version`)
- `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` — the Claude Code plugin manifest
- `Cargo.lock` — regenerated from the manifests so the lock matches

`bump` rewrites the first three and runs `cargo update --workspace` to bring the
lock in line. It edits only the `[package]` version (the first `version =` line
of each `Cargo.toml`), never a dependency's. The spec badge in the README
(`spec-vX.Y`) is a *separate* number — it tracks the `.jd` format, not the
release, and is intentionally left untouched.

`version` is required and must be `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`. Re-run any time; it is
idempotent.

```just
bump version:
  #!/usr/bin/env sh
  set -eu
  case "{{version}}" in
    [0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*) ;;
    *) echo "version must be MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH, got '{{version}}'" >&2; exit 1 ;;
  esac
  root="$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)"
  for f in cli/Cargo.toml core/Cargo.toml; do
    sed -i '0,/^version = .*/s//version = "{{version}}"/' "$root/$f"
  done
  sed -i 's/"version": "[^"]*"/"version": "{{version}}"/' "$root/.claude-plugin/plugin.json"
  ( cd "$root" && cargo update --workspace >/dev/null 2>&1 || true )
  echo "version → {{version}} (cli, core, plugin.json, Cargo.lock)"
```
